RBiofabric Yeast Sif

Robert M Flight

2015-09-04 10:37:09

This is a test of how big a network can be handled by the RBiofabric htmlwidget that @timelyportfolio developed from @wrjl.

Lets try the Yeast High Quality network that @wrjl uses in the landing page of Biofabric itself.

yeast_network <- read.table("yeastHighQuality.sif", sep = " ", header = FALSE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
names(yeast_network) <- c("from", "type", "to")
head(yeast_network)
##      from type      to
## 1 YLR197W   pp YDL014W
## 2 YOR039W   pp YOR061W
## 3 YDR473C   pp YPR178W
## 4 YOR332W   pp YLR447C
## 5 YER090W   pp YKL211C
## 6 YDR394W   pp YGR232W

So this network has 6888 edges, and 3025 nodes.

Lets install RBioFabric.

devtools::install_github("timelyportfolio/RBioFabric")

And create the graph using igraph

library(igraph)
yeast_nodes <- data.frame(name = unique(c(yeast_network[,"from"], yeast_network[,"to"])), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
yeast_graph <- graph_from_data_frame(yeast_network[, c("from", "to")], directed = FALSE, vertices = yeast_nodes)

And lay it out!
